    },
    "question_comments": [],
    "answers": [{
        "owner": {
            "profile_image": "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/4da64399571dbe85911be2c0faf6134a?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG&f=y&so-version=2",
            "account_id": 6800476,
            "user_type": "registered",
            "user_id": 5233942,
            "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/5233942/l-swifter",
            "reputation": 3255,
            "display_name": "L. Swifter",
            "accept_rate": 96
        },
        "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
        "score": 0,
        "is_accepted": false,
        "last_activity_date": 1503022705,
        "creation_date": 1503022705,
        "body": "<p>If you don't need transparency, you can use <code>Bitmap.Config.RGB_565<\/code> instead of <code>Bitmap.Config.ARGB_8888<\/code> : <\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Bitmap.createBitmap(width, height, Bitmap.Config.RGB_565);\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>This reduces memory usage by half.<\/p>\n",
